1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 33 MRSA §2052, sub-§24, ¶B, as amended by PL 2019, c. 571, §3, is
3 further amended by amending subparagraph (1) to read:
4 (1) Money, virtual currency, interest or a dividend, check, draft, deposit or payroll
5 card;
6 Sec. 2. 33 MRSA §2052, sub-§32-A is enacted to read:
7 32-A. Virtual currency. "Virtual currency" means a digital representation of value
8 used as a medium of exchange, unit of account or store of value, which is not legal tender
9 of the United States. "Virtual currency" does not include:
10 A. Software or protocols governing the transfer of a digital representation of value;
11 B. Game-related digital content; or
12 C. A loyalty obligation or gift obligation.
13 Sec. 3. 33 MRSA §2061, sub-§5, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 498, §22, is amended
14 to read:
15 5. Payroll card or demand, savings or time deposit. A payroll card or demand,
16 savings or time deposit, including a deposit that is automatically renewable, 3 years after
17 the later of maturity, if applicable, of the card or deposit and the apparent owner's last
18 indication of interest in the card or deposit, except that a deposit that is automatically
19 renewable is deemed matured on its initial date of maturity unless the apparent owner
20 consented in a record on file with the holder to renewal at or about the time of the renewal;
21 Sec. 4. 33 MRSA §2061, sub-§14, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 498, §22, is amended
22 to read:
23 14. Nonactivated stored-value obligation or electronic payment medium. Funds
24 represented by a nonactivated stored-value obligation or other nonactivated electronic
25 payment medium that require activation for use, one year after the funds would have
26 otherwise first been available to the owner; and
27 Sec. 5. 33 MRSA §2061, sub-§14-A is enacted to read:
28 14-A. Terminated retirement plan. Funds from the termination of a defined
29 contribution plan or other retirement plan, as soon as administratively feasible after the date
30 of plan termination; and
31 Sec. 6. 33 MRSA §2062, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 498, §22, is amended to read:
32 §2062. When tax-deferred or tax-advantaged retirement account presumed
33 abandoned
34 1. Presumed abandoned after 3 years. Subject to section 2070, property held in a
35 pension account or retirement account that qualifies for tax deferral or tax advantage under
36 the income tax laws of the United States is presumed abandoned if it is unclaimed by the
37 apparent owner 3 years after the later of: date a distribution is required under the United
38 States Internal Revenue Code of 1986 in order to avoid a tax penalty, including a
39 distribution required due to the death of the apparent owner, or in the case of a tax-
40 advantaged retirement account, 3 years after the death of the apparent owner.
Page 1 - 132LR0562(01)

1 A. The later of the following dates:
2 (1) Except as in subparagraph (2), the date a communication sent by the holder by
3 first class United States mail to the apparent owner is returned to the holder as
4 undeliverable by the United States Postal Service; and
5 (2) If the returned communication is resent within 30 days, the date the resent
6 communication was returned as undeliverable by the United States Postal Service;
7 and
8 B. The earlier of the following dates:
9 (1) The date the apparent owner becomes 70 1/2 years of age; and
10 (2) If the federal Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, requires distribution
11 to avoid a tax penalty, the date the holder:
12 (a) Receives confirmation of the death of the apparent owner in the ordinary
13 course of its business; or
14 (b) Confirms the death of the apparent owner under subsection 2.
15 2. Confirmation of death of apparent owner. If a holder in the ordinary course of
16 its business receives notice or an indication of the death of an apparent owner and
17 subsection 1, paragraph B applies, the holder shall attempt not later than 90 days after
18 receipt of the notice or indication to confirm whether the apparent owner is deceased.
19 3. Confirmation of apparent owner's interest. If the holder does not send
20 communications to the apparent owner of an account described in subsection 1 by first class
21 United States mail on at least an annual basis, the holder shall attempt to confirm the
22 apparent owner's interest in the property by sending the apparent owner an e-mail not later
23 than 2 years after the apparent owner's last indication of interest in the property. However,
24 the holder promptly shall attempt to contact the apparent owner by first class United States
25 mail if:
26 A. The holder does not have information needed to send the apparent owner an e-mail
27 or the holder believes that the apparent owner's e-mail address in the holder's records
28 is not valid;
29 B. The holder receives notification that the e-mail was not received; or
30 C. The apparent owner does not respond to the e-mail within 30 days after the e-mail
31 was sent.
