12 Sec. 11. 33 MRSA §2067-A is enacted to read:
13 §2067-A. When virtual currency presumed abandoned; liquidation by holder
14 1. Presumed abandoned after 5 years. Virtual currency is presumed abandoned 5
15 years after the last indication of interest by the apparent owner.
16 2. Determination of value; exempt from reporting or liquidation. The
17 administrator may decline to accept virtual currency presumed abandoned if the
18 administrator, in the administrator's discretion, determines that the virtual currency is not
19 freely transferable, is of nominal value or has value that is less than the estimated expenses
20 of maintenance, notice or sale of the property. The administrator may also prescribe by
21 rule classes or types of virtual currency exempt from reporting or liquidation.
22 3. Liquidation of unclaimed virtual currency. A holder of unclaimed virtual
23 currency shall liquidate the virtual currency within 30 days prior to the filing of the report
24 under section 2091 and remit the proceeds to the administrator.
25 4. Liquidation not possible. If a holder of unclaimed virtual currency reasonably
26 believes that the holder cannot liquidate the virtual currency and cannot otherwise cause
27 the virtual currency to be liquidated, the holder shall promptly notify the administrator in
28 writing and explain the reasons why the virtual currency cannot be liquidated as otherwise
29 required under subsection 3. The administrator shall then direct the holder concerning an
30 alternate disposition of the virtual currency.
31 5. State and holder held harmless. An apparent owner does not have recourse against
32 the administrator or a holder of unclaimed virtual currency to recover any gain in value that
33 occurs after the liquidation of the virtual currency under subsection 3. Consistent with
34 section 2114, subsection 2, the administrator shall defend and indemnify a holder against
35 liability on any such claim, as long as the holder has acted in good faith and substantially
36 complied with sections 2101 and 2102.
