22 Sec. 15. 33 MRSA §2071, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 498, §22, is amended to read:
23 §2071. Deposit account for proceeds of insurance policy or annuity
24 If proceeds payable under a life or endowment insurance policy or annuity contract are
25 deposited into an account with check-writing or draft-writing privileges for the beneficiary
26 of the policy or contract and, under a supplementary contract not involving annuity benefits
27 other than death benefits, the proceeds are retained by the insurance company or the
28 financial organization where the account is held, the policy or contract includes the assets
29 in the account, and the account proceeds are presumed abandoned in accordance with
30 section 2061, subsection 7, or 3 years after the beneficiary's last indication of interest in the
31 account, whichever is later.
