30 Sec. 23. 33 MRSA §2121 is enacted to read:
31 §2121. Property held in trust
32 A holder that, on May 1st for insurance property and stored-value obligations and
33 November 1st for all other property types, holds property presumed abandoned under
34 subchapter 2 holds the property in trust for the benefit of the State on behalf of the missing
35 owner and is liable to the State for the full value of the property, plus any accrued interest
36 and penalty as defined in section 2194. A holder is not required by this section to segregate
37 or establish trust accounts for the property as long as the property is timely delivered to the
38 administrator in accordance with section 2113.
