25 §2214. Confidentiality agreement
26 A person to be examined under section 2162 may require, as a condition of disclosure
27 of the records of the person to be examined, that the administrator or the administrator's
28 agent execute and deliver to the person to be examined a confidentiality agreement that:
29 1. Form. Is in a standard form that is reasonably satisfactory to approved for use by
30 the administrator; and
31 2. Compliance with subchapter. Requires the person having access to the records to
32 comply with the provisions of this subchapter applicable to the person.
33 If the person to be examined elects not to execute a confidentiality agreement that has
34 been approved for use by the administrator, and the person to be examined is unable to
35 reach agreement on the terms of a confidentiality agreement within 90 days of the
36 administrator's authorization of the examination, the examination must proceed without a
37 confidentiality agreement in place and the person to be examined must rely upon the
38 confidentiality provisions of this subchapter.
Page 7 - 132LR0562(01)

1 SUMMARY
22 This bill makes the following changes to the Maine Revised Unclaimed Property Act.
3 1. It adds "virtual currency" as a property type and provisions regarding presumed
4 abandonment and liquidation and defines the term.
5 2. It simplifies the presumption of abandonment process for tax-advantaged retirement
6 accounts and other tax-deferred accounts.
7 3. It simplifies the presumption of abandonment for custodial accounts for minors to
8 not be remitted to the administrator until the owner is no longer a minor.
9 4. It simplifies the presumption of abandonment for security accounts.
10 5. It removes automatic transactions as an indication of an apparent owner's interest in
11 presumed abandoned property.
12 6. It prohibits charging escheat fees on certain accounts.
13 7. It clarifies when an audit has commenced.
14 8. It requires unremitted property to be held in trust on behalf of the owner and not a
15 part of bankruptcy assets.
16 9. It protects the confidentiality of the unclaimed property owner's data.
17 10. It strengthens confidentiality laws for 3rd-party auditors.
